Passlib is an open-source Python library that provides a unified interface for password hashing and verification. It supports a wide range of secure hashing algorithms

python-jose
Used to create and verify JWT tokens (JSON Web Tokens)
After login, instead of sending password every time: gives tokens
user logs in → gets token → uses token for future requests
This Create tokens, Verify tokens, Decode payload (user info)

from jose import jwt
sectre_key = "abc123"
Algorithm = "SHA256"
#create token 
token  =jwt.encode({"user: "chihnitha"},secret_key , algorithm=Algorithm})
#decode
data = jwt.decode( token,secret_key,algorithm=[Algorithm])

In a real system:

1️⃣ Signup
Hash password using passlib
Store in DB
2️⃣ Login
Verify password using passlib
If correct → create JWT using python-jose
3️⃣ Future requests
Client sends JWT
Server verifies using python-jose

User → Signup → hash password → store

User → Login → verify password → generate JWT

User → API request → send JWT → verify → allow access
